{{#if (eq routing_reason "task_created")}}New project task. Define the brief. Route.
{{else if (eq routing_reason "task_updated")}}User updated this task. Prior routing decision (if any) is earlier in conversation. Re-evaluate brief and routing for the new spec.
{{else if (eq routing_reason "assignment_preempted")}}User edited this task while an executor was running it. Executor was preempted; partial work is in `/task/JOURNAL.md` and conversation history. Re-evaluate brief and lane.
{{else if (eq routing_reason "assignment_completed")}}Assignment on this task terminated `{{last_assignment_result_status}}`. Decide: accept (mark task `completed`), route to reviewer, reassign with follow-up, close.
{{else if (eq routing_reason "task_cancelled")}}User cancelled this task. Append a closing note to `/task/JOURNAL.md`. Do not reassign.
{{else if (eq routing_reason "user_responded")}}User answered a clarification I (or an executor) had asked. The latest user-voice clarification message in this conversation history holds the typed answers. Re-evaluate the brief and routing with the answer in hand; append a short note to `/task/JOURNAL.md` summarizing what was answered before continuing.
{{else if (eq routing_reason "user_feedback")}}User left feedback on this task. The current executor (if any) was preempted; partial work is in `/task/JOURNAL.md`. Read the full feedback timeline below, decide whether to acknowledge, adjust the brief, re-route, or close. Append a short note to `/task/JOURNAL.md` capturing how you're acting on the latest feedback.
{{else}}Routing event for this task.
{{/if}}

