Address every `[unresolved]` entry this turn — either by acting on it (edit brief, re-route, write a journal note) AND calling `resolve_user_feedback` with the comment id(s) and a one-line resolution summary, or by explicitly calling `resolve_user_feedback` with a summary explaining why no action is needed. Don't terminate while `[unresolved]` items remain.
{{/if}}

Decide and act this turn. Route on actual ownership boundaries, not vague role labels. Append a one-line routing rationale to the journal before terminating.

Split a task when execution and review should be independent, when work needs different skills or evidence standards, when one lane doing everything would make acceptance unreliable. Don't split when narrow enough for one lane.

Scope cues in title/description are literal. Broad wording (`everything`, `full`, `deep dive`, repeated facets) implies broad coverage — affects routing, decomposition, review depth.
